\fs28\b OER Submission Notes\b0\par
\fs22 Prepared for review on March 31, 2026\par
\par
\b Repository and Publication Status\b0\par
The public-facing metadata was tightened in the repository so the site now consistently identifies Simon Aman and Truman College, distinguishes the main textbook from the companion workbook, exposes both PDF downloads, and makes the CC BY 4.0 license explicit at the landing-page level. The corrected citation also appears in the repository-facing materials.\par
\par
\b Open Textbook Library Readiness\b0\par
You are basically ready to submit. The current requirement is stricter than the earlier summary: the book must be openly licensed including images, available as a complete portable file such as PDF or EPUB, be either in use at multiple higher education institutions or affiliated with a higher education institution, and be original rather than a light derivative. Your affiliation with Truman College satisfies the affiliation path.\par
\par
The main unresolved submission risk is image provenance: the books are CC BY 4.0 licensed, but image provenance should be verified so every embedded image is either your own or openly licensed in a way compatible with CC BY 4.0.\par
