\b Submission-Risk Review\b0\par
\par
\b 1. Image licensing remains the main material risk.\b0\par
If any screenshot, diagram, or embedded image came from another source, make sure you have permission or a compatible open license.\par
\par
\b 2. Open Textbook Library will likely treat the textbook as the primary submission.\b0\par
The workbook should be framed as ancillary or companion material, which is already how the landing page and README present it.\par
\par
\b 3. The site and repository metadata are now aligned, but a final editorial pass is still worth doing.\b0\par
Minor manuscript wording issues are not a licensing blocker, but polishing them will improve the submission.\par
\par
\b Natural Next Steps\b0\par
\par
1. Submit the main textbook to Open Textbook Library using the text above.\par
2. Submit the same main textbook to MERLOT and OER Commons, listing the workbook as a companion resource.\par
3. Do one final image-rights audit before submission if any figures were not created by you.\par
